cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.SE, cs.CE 

This paper involves the development of an AI system that uses automated reasoning and deep reinforcement learning technologies to synthesize operation procedures for chemical plants. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with the control and optimization of complex and dynamical systems, which suggests that it could belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the use of a chemical plant simulator, which could place it in the cs.SE (Software Engineering) category. Finally, the paper deals with chemical plants, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.CE (Chemical Engineering) category.
